for most of that time,

13:43.959 --> 13:46.250
less than one-tenth of the
profits seems more than fair.

13:46.333 --> 13:47.959
Might be. But then again,
I was the client.

13:48.041 --> 13:50.959
So you're kind of comparing
apples to my money.

13:51.041 --> 13:51.500
I did more
than just run your money.

13:51.583 --> 13:52.834
I kept us alive.

13:52.917 --> 13:55.417
I killed it
at the Idea Dinner.

13:55.500 --> 13:57.333
I convinced the Street
that night, and every day since,

13:57.417 --> 13:59.417
that there was always
someone at the helm.

13:59.500 --> 14:00.333
I got us
through a natural disaster.

14:00.417 --> 14:02.583
I all but closed Kansas City
before Ben Kim

14:02.667 --> 14:04.458
went Thunder From Down Under
on them.

14:04.542 --> 14:05.959
And let's not forget
that I was key in making up

14:06.041 --> 14:07.959
the shortfall
from Grigor's redemption,

14:08.041 --> 14:10.125
at great personal cost.

14:10.208 --> 14:11.750
Still sore about Oscar?

14:13.250 --> 14:15.792
Yet here I am, still ready
to help lock down the raise.

14:15.875 --> 14:17.583
About that.
No, you're not.

14:17.667 --> 14:20.083
I don't actually need you
in the pitches.

14:20.166 --> 14:22.041
For one thing, you bombed
your first raise meeting,

14:22.125 --> 14:23.959
with Grigor's lieutenant,
bombed it on purpose.

14:24.041 --> 14:25.625
And for another:
the investors need to know

14:25.709 --> 14:27.667
that you're here
at Axe Cap,

14:27.750 --> 14:31.375
that someone's
"always at the helm."

14:31.458 --> 14:34.250
Besides...
the raise is my thing.

14:34.333 --> 14:35.667
I'm thinking
that the final number

14:35.750 --> 14:38.375
will be something just shy of
half of what you're looking for.

14:38.458 --> 14:39.917
I don't agree.
This isn't heavy petting

14:40.000 --> 14:41.875
on the Oberlin campus:
we don't both have to agree.

14:41.959 --> 14:43.208
I say what it is.
You take it.

14:43.291 --> 14:44.709
Yes, that is so.
But still. I don't accept.

14:44.792 --> 14:47.375
I never made that much
at your age.

14:47.458 --> 14:48.208
I've accomplished
more than you had.

14:48.291 --> 14:50.250
But you don't have
your own shop.

14:50.333 --> 14:51.291
If you were ready
for that,

14:51.375 --> 14:53.083
we wouldn't be having
this conversation,

14:53.166 --> 14:55.625
I'd be looking at a
Taylor-shaped hole in the wall.

14:55.709 --> 14:59.166
Twenty is as much as anybody's
ever gotten out of me.

14:59.250 --> 15:00.625
Learn to be rich on that.

15:00.709 --> 15:03.125
And I was beginning to think
you were done teaching me.

15:03.208 --> 15:04.875
♪ dramatic music ♪

15:04.959 --> 15:06.083
Let's finish this later.

15:08.333 --> 15:10.458
♪♪♪

15:10.542 --> 15:13.000
♪♪♪

15:15.291 --> 15:19.166
♪♪♪

15:19.250 --> 15:23.166
♪♪♪

15:23.250 --> 15:27.125
♪♪♪

15:27.208 --> 15:31.083
♪♪♪

15:31.166 --> 15:35.000
♪♪♪

15:35.083 --> 15:38.959
♪♪♪

15:39.041 --> 15:40.500
I'd like half a million.

15:40.583 --> 15:41.917
You just got here.
Your signing bonus is your comp.

15:42.000 --> 15:44.291
I didn't say
I deserved half a million.

15:44.375 --> 15:45.542
But you rarely get
what you don't ask for.

15:45.625 --> 15:47.041
So I'm fucking asking.

15:47.125 --> 15:48.667
Otherwise,
why are we doing this?

15:48.750 --> 15:50.333
We've never talked
one-on-one.

15:50.417 --> 15:51.709
I wanted to get a hit
off of you.

15:51.792 --> 15:53.125
I hit like
the Purple People Eaters.

15:53.208 --> 15:54.542
So be careful
what you wish for.

15:54.625 --> 15:56.041
Oh.
This is gonna be fun.

15:56.125 --> 15:58.041
I believe
I've proved my value.

15:58.125 --> 15:59.750
Don't need to justify a thing
to you at this point.

15:59.834 --> 16:01.500
Oooh, working stiff.

16:01.583 --> 16:03.542
Just like your personal totem,
The Undertaker.

16:03.625 --> 16:04.583
Do you have people
feeding you this shit

16:04.667 --> 16:05.500
about us ahead of time?

16:05.583 --> 16:08.250
Thing is,
for the last couple of weeks,

16:08.333 --> 16:09.875
I haven't really felt
your presence.

16:09.959 --> 16:11.208
You saying
I've been coasting.

16:11.291 --> 16:14.291
I'm saying there's
no garbage time at Axe Capital.

16:14.375 --> 16:16.667
Every minute
of every quarter matters.

16:16.750 --> 16:18.667
No scrubs
get playing time.

16:18.750 --> 16:21.166
And even if you are my MVP
at the All-Star break,

16:21.250 --> 16:23.667
if you stop performing,
you will be replaced.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.166
Pay me
what you're gonna pay me.

16:25.250 --> 16:26.792
Save the pep talks
for someone who needs 'em.

16:26.875 --> 16:29.458
I think I like
that version of you.

16:29.542 --> 16:31.709
But I could hate it
another time.

16:31.792 --> 16:34.208
Ok. What you did
with the Wendy thing aside,

16:34.291 --> 16:36.125
and it's hard
to put it aside,

16:36.208 --> 16:38.875
I'm paying you 1.3,
a personal record.

16:38.959 --> 16:40.375
On top of
your other bonus

16:40.458 --> 16:42.125
that's more than a two-ball
for this year.

16:42.208 --> 16:43.917
But that is not
a repeatable trick.

16:44.000 --> 16:45.709
When we're here 12 months
from now,

16:45.792 --> 16:47.542
if you're not still
bodyslamming like... uh...

16:47.625 --> 16:49.834
King Kong Bundy...

16:49.917 --> 16:50.959
Did you pretend
not to remember that

16:51.041 --> 16:51.667
to make me feel good?

16:51.750 --> 16:54.875
Goodbye Mafee.

16:54.959 --> 16:58.208
I think... I should not
throw out the first number.

16:58.291 --> 17:00.583
Because I have a tendency
to undervalue myself.

17:00.667 --> 17:02.291
I'd like to make you
a PM.

17:02.375 --> 17:03.792
Portfolio Manager?

17:03.875 --> 17:04.792
I would have gone
Prime Minister,

17:04.875 --> 17:07.083
but there you go,
undervaluing.

17:07.166 --> 17:08.583
-Meet the new salary,

17:08.667 --> 17:10.500
same as the old salary.

17:10.583 --> 17:13.250
I'm a PM.

17:13.333 --> 17:16.458
♪♪♪

17:18.166 --> 17:20.083
I've asked
my special counsel,

17:20.166 --> 17:21.834
Bryan Connerty,
to sit in.

17:21.917 --> 17:23.500
We meet again, young man.

17:23.583 --> 17:24.458
The Axelrod case.

17:24.542 --> 17:26.667
Yeah.

17:26.750 --> 17:29.500
That thing was like
cleaning out intestines

17:29.583 --> 17:32.291
before you eat 'em,
a giant fucking waste of time.

17:32.375 --> 17:36.750
But I'm here to speak
of something more concerning.

17:36.834 --> 17:38.291
It has come to my attention
that there are men

17:38.375 --> 17:42.709
and probably women,
within the Federal B-I,

17:42.792 --> 17:44.125
perhaps even
within this very office,

17:44.208 --> 17:46.125
who are undermining
our sacred purpose.

17:46.208 --> 17:48.208
-Which is...
-I don't know if it's

17:48.291 --> 17:49.500
some Deep State bullshit,

17:49.583 --> 17:51.875
or just some vigilantes
who think they know better,

17:51.959 --> 17:53.291
leaking to the press,
and causing

17:53.375 --> 17:54.792
Lord knows
what other ruckus.

17:54.875 --> 17:57.000
I will keep a lookout
for what the Lord knows.

17:57.083 --> 17:59.291
The Lord knows all, madam.
Took care of that for you.

17:59.375 --> 18:02.458
As for the rest,
I want a hard-target search

18:02.542 --> 18:06.000
of every e-mail, text message,
and online footprint

18:06.083 --> 18:09.417
so we know who's trustworthy
and who needs to be purged.

18:09.500 --> 18:11.625
I'm just not sure
it's strictly legal for us

18:11.709 --> 18:12.458
to undertake
this ourselves,

18:12.542 --> 18:14.667
or if it's too gray
of an area.

18:14.750 --> 18:16.625
Maybe it would be best to have
a court order first--

18:16.709 --> 18:18.500
We can do it.

18:18.583 --> 18:20.333
And if you want to stay
out of the deep gray,

18:20.417 --> 18:23.417
Director Lynch,
I can lead the review myself.

18:23.500 --> 18:26.875
You know, chart a--
a whiter shade of pale.

18:26.959 --> 18:29.000
Impressive.

18:29.083 --> 18:32.166
All too often I am told
of obstacles and regulations

18:32.250 --> 18:35.208
when what I really wanna hear
is "sí, se puede"

18:38.000 --> 18:42.125
Ira,
uh, this is Pete Decker.

18:42.208 --> 18:44.417
He's in the health
and conditioning industry.

18:44.500 --> 18:45.917
Is this a bailout?

18:46.000 --> 18:47.291
More like an intervention.

18:48.709 --> 18:49.959
Tell him
what you told me, Pete.

18:50.041 --> 18:53.041
"The bitch is a booster.
The bitch is a born thief."

18:53.125 --> 18:56.083
You talking about my wife?
You looked into her?

18:56.166 --> 19:00.625
She needed looking into,
so I looked. Go on.

19:00.709 --> 19:04.458
Her business is...
well, there is no business.

19:04.542 --> 19:06.375
Everything you gave her
was transferred

19:06.458 --> 19:09.208
into the account of her
supposed business partner,

19:09.291 --> 19:10.959
Anthony Radaelli.

19:11.041 --> 19:12.291
I assume they,
you know...

19:15.500 --> 19:17.542
Thank you.

19:17.625 --> 19:18.875
Do right by me, Chuck.

19:18.959 --> 19:20.709
My middle name.

19:24.583 --> 19:26.208
I know
this is hard to hear.

19:26.291 --> 19:28.250
The commercial property

19:28.333 --> 19:29.750
she told you
she plunked down on,

19:29.834 --> 19:31.959
that doesn't exist either.

19:32.041 --> 19:36.709
But there's an apartment,

19:36.792 --> 19:38.000
a very expensive apartment,

19:38.083 --> 19:42.667
they're about to close on.

19:42.750 --> 19:46.000
I'm sorry.

19:46.083 --> 19:48.583
Yeah...

19:48.667 --> 19:51.417
You knew.

19:51.500 --> 19:53.083
Yeah. Some.
The rest I suspected.

19:53.166 --> 19:56.458
Oh, boy.
To carry that around...

19:56.542 --> 19:57.875
Fucking kills me.

19:59.375 --> 20:01.417
But, uh, you know,
Chuck,

20:01.500 --> 20:02.417
I know you're only trying
to help,

20:02.500 --> 20:03.583
but please
stay out of it.

20:03.667 --> 20:06.166
It's, um...

20:06.250 --> 20:07.500
There's no prenup.

20:07.583 --> 20:08.291
And New York's
a no-fault state.

20:08.375 --> 20:11.083
And I'd be halved
financially.

20:11.166 --> 20:14.083
There's no prenup?

20:14.166 --> 20:17.333
Oh, Ira,
you're a fucking lawyer.

20:17.417 --> 20:18.458
For once
I didn't want to be.

20:18.542 --> 20:19.792
I wanted to be a romantic.

20:19.875 --> 20:23.542
Mm.
I still do.

20:23.625 --> 20:25.041
I gave up
on a marriage once.

20:25.125 --> 20:27.125
I've regretted it
every day since.

20:27.208 --> 20:30.625
I'm not giving up
this time.

20:30.709 --> 20:32.250
It'll blow over.

20:32.333 --> 20:35.792
She's young.
It's a last hurrah.

20:35.875 --> 20:37.000
You know, she'll get
whatever it is out of her system

20:37.083 --> 20:41.333
and then...
then she'll come home.

20:41.417 --> 20:44.709
♪ dramatic music ♪

20:49.750 --> 20:54.083
♪ mid-tempo music ♪

20:54.166 --> 20:58.959
♪♪♪

20:59.041 --> 21:03.792
♪♪♪

21:03.875 --> 21:08.667
♪♪♪

21:08.750 --> 21:12.750
♪♪♪

21:12.834 --> 21:18.250
♪♪♪

21:29.458 --> 21:30.333
I really have to watch
what I tell you.

21:30.417 --> 21:32.375
It's like you're listening
to every word.

21:32.458 --> 21:34.542
Especially when you start
talking about

21:34.625 --> 21:37.542
hiding out in bathtubs.

21:37.625 --> 21:39.625
And places that remind you
of what that felt like.

21:39.709 --> 21:41.834
I wasn't hiding. It's just that
when I was younger

21:41.917 --> 21:43.208
the bathtub was the only place
I could go

21:43.291 --> 21:44.875
to be alone and think.

21:44.959 --> 21:46.542
I'd press myself
against the sides so hard

21:46.625 --> 21:47.542
eventually my legs
would go numb.

21:47.625 --> 21:50.208
Then I'd start thinking
I didn't have legs,

21:50.291 --> 21:51.750
and I'd wish for fins.

21:51.834 --> 21:54.625
Because then not fitting in
would make more sense.

21:54.709 --> 21:55.625
I get it.

21:55.709 --> 21:58.166
I almost feel like
a mermaid here.

21:58.250 --> 22:01.208
♪ dramatic music ♪

22:01.291 --> 22:04.583
♪♪♪

22:04.667 --> 22:06.542
Comp didn't go the way
you wanted.

22:06.625 --> 22:09.208
He said I was
off the raise team.

22:09.291 --> 22:11.667
Is he punishing me for doing
exactly what he asked of me?

22:11.750 --> 22:13.041
Axe doesn't punish people.
Unless they've wronged him.

22:13.125 --> 22:15.709
Or Lara. Or his kids.

22:15.792 --> 22:17.208
Or me.

22:17.291 --> 22:20.000
Or the New York
Football Giants.

22:20.083 --> 22:22.083
I won't stagnate.

22:22.166 --> 22:24.750
Not for Axe.
Not for anybody.

22:24.834 --> 22:26.417
You know Axe has never changed
a comp decision.

22:26.500 --> 22:29.375
So I've heard.
And I might be able to live

22:29.458 --> 22:30.917
with the number
he can live with.

22:31.000 --> 22:33.750
But what I need is
forward momentum,

22:33.834 --> 22:36.083
above all things,
even money.

22:36.166 --> 22:37.834
♪♪♪

22:37.917 --> 22:40.000
Yes. You do.

22:40.083 --> 22:43.458
I'll talk to him.

22:43.542 --> 22:45.333
Give me a day.

22:45.417 --> 22:48.333
♪♪♪

22:48.417 --> 22:50.834
♪♪♪

22:50.917 --> 22:55.083
♪♪♪

22:55.166 --> 22:58.625
♪♪♪

23:00.166 --> 23:01.792
Kvankam.

23:01.875 --> 23:04.291
Although.

23:04.375 --> 23:05.792
Pensis.

23:05.875 --> 23:07.291
Thought.

23:07.375 --> 23:08.625
Comp.

23:08.709 --> 23:11.291
Kompenso.

23:11.375 --> 23:13.500
So you're not here to help me
with my Esperanto.

23:13.583 --> 23:16.458
I haven't had my comp meeting
scheduled yet.

23:16.542 --> 23:18.125
Must be an oversight.

23:18.208 --> 23:19.667
Must be.

23:23.959 --> 23:25.166
Axe, you remember
Ari Spyros.

23:25.250 --> 23:27.083
Works down in Compliance.

23:27.166 --> 23:29.625
Uh. Rings a bell.

23:29.709 --> 23:33.125
But like children of the 1800s,
seen and not heard.

23:33.208 --> 23:34.125
And not even seen,
you know?

23:34.208 --> 23:36.375
Spyros was concerned
that his comp meeting

23:36.458 --> 23:37.750
wasn't on the books.

23:37.834 --> 23:39.166
I am sure
it's an oversight.

23:39.250 --> 23:41.625
Was it an oversight?

23:41.709 --> 23:44.041
Compliance does not get
performance-related comp.

23:44.125 --> 23:45.834
-Oh.
-Sure. Usually.

23:45.917 --> 23:49.917
But Compliance doesn't usually
turn around a shop overnight.

23:50.000 --> 23:52.000
But before I got here
this place was dirtier

23:52.083 --> 23:54.834
than the porta potty outside
a third-rate donkey show.

23:54.917 --> 23:56.250
Arrests, fines,

23:56.333 --> 24:00.333
investigations
up the wazoo.

24:00.417 --> 24:03.667
And since the Greek Freak
has been on the scene--

24:03.750 --> 24:04.458
You cannot
call yourself that.

24:04.542 --> 24:07.166
There is no bonus
for Compliance.

24:07.250 --> 24:09.375
What about
the other stuff?

24:09.458 --> 24:12.333
Extracurricular stuff...

24:12.417 --> 24:15.291
I'm talking about the stuff
in Bill's other garage.

24:15.375 --> 24:18.500
Doesn't Ari get
to wet his beak?

24:18.583 --> 24:21.625
Ohh.
I forgot about that...

24:21.709 --> 24:24.041
That reminds me of
where you were

24:24.125 --> 24:26.250
right before you decided
to share that little brainstorm.

24:26.333 --> 24:29.208
Fired.
Halfway out the door.

24:29.291 --> 24:31.083
Three quarters.
Literally.

24:31.166 --> 24:32.709
Dead to me.

24:32.792 --> 24:36.000
No, your comp
is getting your job back.

24:36.083 --> 24:37.458
Getting to hiss
and tinker

24:37.542 --> 24:39.625
with your little
espresso erector set

24:39.709 --> 24:40.375
rather than pick
through the Dumpster

24:40.458 --> 24:42.208
for your
mangled steam wand.

24:42.291 --> 24:43.709
-I see...
-If we were to do

24:43.792 --> 24:46.709
a little accounting of how much
you meant to Axe Cap,

24:46.792 --> 24:49.291
we would first have to look
at what you cost me

24:49.375 --> 24:50.458
by turning Wendy in.

24:50.542 --> 24:54.208
The consequences
of your "chaos grenade."

24:54.291 --> 24:56.208
[whistles,
imitates explosion]

24:56.291 --> 24:58.166
Yeah. To say nothing
of the nightmare

24:58.250 --> 24:59.041
that you plunged her into,

24:59.125 --> 25:02.083
and the unthinkable acts
I had to perform

25:02.166 --> 25:04.166
in order
to set things right.

25:04.250 --> 25:06.250
I mean
dollars and cents alone.

25:06.333 --> 25:10.417
The fines, the bonuses,
the jet fuel to Nova Scotia,

25:10.500 --> 25:15.125
you owe me
1.195 million dollars.

25:15.208 --> 25:16.041
You know what?

25:16.125 --> 25:17.417
I don't think
I need a comp meeting.

25:17.500 --> 25:19.625
My-- My base
is very generous,

25:19.709 --> 25:24.375
and I think we should
just leave it right there.

25:26.959 --> 25:29.417
That was the full
Signor Roberto.

25:29.500 --> 25:32.083
"The rent
stays like before."

25:32.166 --> 25:33.750
Yeah.
That's the first comp meeting

25:33.834 --> 25:34.583
I've actually enjoyed.

25:34.667 --> 25:37.333
You know,
I'm tempted to fire

25:37.417 --> 25:38.875
the whole
fucking lot of them.

25:38.959 --> 25:40.917
Except maybe like two.

25:41.000 --> 25:42.250
But someone has got
to roll the coins up

25:42.333 --> 25:43.500
into those little sleeves.

25:43.583 --> 25:44.458
Yeah.
Practically all they do.

25:44.542 --> 25:47.125
Nah, you can't fire 'em,
estro.

25:47.208 --> 25:49.125
Right before the raise,
it'll look like panic.

25:49.208 --> 25:51.166
Like there's not enough grain to
get everyone through the winter.

25:51.250 --> 25:52.125
I know.

25:52.208 --> 25:54.291
So I'm not doing it...

25:54.375 --> 25:56.625
But, you know, when I'm sitting
across the table from them

25:56.709 --> 25:57.458
and I see
their hungry little mouths,

25:57.542 --> 26:00.208
they're people,
sure, my people,

26:00.291 --> 26:02.125
and I love 'em
most of the year.

26:02.208 --> 26:05.333
But today,
all I can see is

26:05.417 --> 26:07.458
their snapping
fucking mouths,

26:07.542 --> 26:09.625
and instead of wanting
to feed 'em,

26:09.709 --> 26:11.125
I just want to punch
their teeth in.

26:11.208 --> 26:13.083
♪ dramatic music ♪

26:13.166 --> 26:17.208
♪♪♪

26:26.542 --> 26:28.709
The rest of them are scared
to come in when I'm in here.

26:28.792 --> 26:32.208
I clocked you going in
about 20 minutes ago,

26:32.291 --> 26:33.875
I figured this was as close
to a Beta state

26:33.959 --> 26:34.417
as I'll ever find you in.

26:34.500 --> 26:38.709
Mm.
What then?

26:38.792 --> 26:40.375
You've got
personnel problems.

26:40.458 --> 26:41.583
That's what they'd all
like you to think.

26:41.667 --> 26:42.667
None of 'em
are going anywhere.

26:42.750 --> 26:46.166
I'm talking about one person
in particular.

26:46.250 --> 26:47.500
Taylor is about to get paid
the same as James Harden.

26:47.583 --> 26:49.875
You think they can't get by
on that?

26:49.959 --> 26:50.959
It's not about money.

26:51.041 --> 26:52.333
They keep demanding
more of it.

26:52.417 --> 26:53.959
Because you're not giving them
what's more important

26:54.041 --> 26:55.542
than money.
So money is all that's left.

26:55.625 --> 26:57.834
Well, I'm about to adopt
the official policy

